frameDefinitions: An Agent, which may be an individual or group, is engaged in a complex Activity.
A Complex with a particular Function is formed out of Component_entities.
This frame describes a complex event which lasts some amount of time, consisting of a beginning stage, a stage where the process is ongoing, and a finish or end.
This frame concerns permanent organizations (the Institutions) that are intended to help members of the Target_group in a particular Domain with a Service_action.
An Agent or Cause causes a Process or State to end.
This frame is for words that denote highly schematic entities.
